Eco-Bat Technologies Reports 87% Jump in Second Quarter Profit

-- B y   C l a u d i a   C a r p e n t e r
-- 
2011-08-26T07:00:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/eco-bat-technologies-reports-87-jump-in-second-quarter-profit.html
Eco-Bat Technologies Ltd. , the
largest lead producer in  Europe  and  South Africa , reported an 87
percent jump in second quarter profit.  Net income rose to 36.5 million pounds ($59.6 million) in
the three months ended June 30 from 19.58 million pounds in the
same period last year, the Matlock, England-based company said
in an e-mailed report today. Revenue jumped 25 percent to 471.1
million pounds.  Lead for delivery in three months averaged 28 percent
higher over the period, and was at $2,393 a metric ton at
7:58 a.m. in London. Eco-Bat sold 207,000 tons of lead in the
period, up from 203,000 tons a year earlier, the company said.  ((Eco-Bat will hold a conference call at 2 p.m. U.K. time.
